      "height": 60
    },
    {
      "id": "n_wdt_dml_wdt_rationale_75",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "Lazily computes the current count from the cycles elapsed since the last update, scaled by the clock divider. Returns 0 once the counter has underflowed, and the stored value while the timer _1a8c53b9.md",
      "x": 3040,
      "y": 160,
      "width": 180,
      "height": 60
    },
    {
      "id": "n_wdt_dml_wdt_rationale_111",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "Maps the WDOGCONTROL.STEP_VALUE field to the clock divider (124816), defaulting to 1 for reserved encodings. The divider sets how many input clock cycles correspond to one decrement of the wa_7eaa5102.md",
      "x": 3240,
      "y": 160,
      "width": 180,
      "height": 60
    },
    {
      "id": "n_wdt_dml_wdt_rationale_105",
